{
  "_comment": [
    "CLEAR BTV camera configuration.",
    "",
    "Top-level key: BTV device name as it appears in the BTVDC FESA instantiation XML (e.g. 'CA.BTV0810').",
    "",
    "Fields:",
    "  digiCamDevice       – FESA device name of the associated DigiCam (image source).",
    "  rotate              – number of 90-degree CCW turns applied to the raw image (0-3).",
    "  flip_hor            – mirror horizontally before display (0 or 1).",
    "  flip_ver            – mirror vertically before display (0 or 1).",
    "  controlDeviceName   – FESA device name of the filter/lamp controller, null if none.",
    "  controlDeviceType   – controller family string, e.g. 'BTVCTRL'. null if no controller.",
    "  controlDeviceFields – type-specific controller parameters (object, empty when no controller).",
    "                        BTVCTRL: { 'system': 1 or 2 }  (which DCM sub-system to address)",
    "                        Other types will add their own fields here without changing the schema.",
    "  fixValueLamps       – true/false/null (null = unknown, device not in any parsed XML).",
    "  filterInstalled     – whether a filter wheel is present.",
    "  firstLampInstalled  – whether lamp 1 is present.",
    "  screenInstalled     – whether the screen mechanism is physically present.",
    "  secondLampInstalled – whether lamp 2 is present.",
    "",
    "  screenMoverDevice   – FESA device that moves the screen, or null.",
    "                        null  → screen is driven by the standard BTVCTRL screen command (most devices).",
    "                        str   → custom mover device; use screenMoverType/Fields for routing.",
    "  screenMoverType     – device family of the custom mover, e.g. 'BStepMotorVME'. null for standard.",
    "  screenMoverFields   – type-specific mover parameters, or null for standard devices.",
    "                        BStepMotorVME: { 'setpoints': { label: integer_value, ... } }",
    "                        The set/get FESA property names for each mover type are fixed",
    "                        constants in the Python code (not stored here).",
    "                        CA.BTV0875 note: screen uses CA.AIR-TS.BOX1.01 (BStepMotorVME);",
    "                        the BTVCTRL still handles filter and lamps for that device.",
    "",
    "Devices marked 'XML source: BTVConc_DU.cfv-2010-btvclex1.xml' were extracted automatically.",
    "CS.* devices are retained from the previous config; hardware-installed fields are unknown."
  ],

